text: Abramovka () is a rural locality (a selo) in Izvestkovskoye Urban Settlement of Obluchensky District, Jewish Autonomous Oblast, Russia. The population was 1 as of 2010. == Geography == The village is located on Trans-Siberian Railway, 2 km north from R297 highway. == References == Category:Rural localities in the Jewish Autonomous Oblast
title: Abramovka, Jewish Autonomous Oblast
